						<note resp="Philip Lampi">"The four votes for Mr. Daggett as Senator, were given by his Honor, the Lieut. Governor, the Hon. Messrs. Wolcott, Brace and Perkins.  Mr. Lanman had five votes and Mr. Bristol, one.  The Hon. Mr. Boardman voted Mr. Bristol, Mr. Chapman was absent, and Mr. Lanman withdrew when the Bill was read."  Connecticut Mirror (Hartford, CT).  November 2, 1818.</note>
